# SSH / OPENSSH

## Installation serveur SSH

```bash
apt update
apt install openssh-server -y
```

## Vérifier le service

```bash
systemctl status ssh
systemctl restart ssh
```

---

# CONNEXION SSH

## Connexion

```bash
ssh user@IP_SERVEUR
```

Exemple :

```bash
ssh melissa@192.168.1.10
```

## Quitter

```bash
exit
```

---

# CONFIGURATION SSH

## Fichier principal

```bash
nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
```

## Changer le port

```bash
Port 2222
```

## Désactiver l'authentification par mot de passe

```bash
PasswordAuthentication no
```

## Appliquer

```bash
systemctl restart ssh
```

---

# CLÉS SSH

## Générer une paire de clés

```bash
ssh-keygen
```

## Copier la clé publique

```bash
ssh-copy-id user@IP_SERVEUR
```

## Connexion avec clé

```bash
ssh user@IP_SERVEUR
```

---

# SCP (COPIE DE FICHIERS)

## Client → Serveur

```bash
scp fichier.txt user@IP_SERVEUR:~
```

## Serveur → Client

```bash
scp user@IP_SERVEUR:/home/user/fichier.txt .
```

## Copier un dossier

```bash
scp -r dossier user@IP_SERVEUR:~
```

---

# SFTP

## Connexion

```bash
sftp user@IP_SERVEUR
```

## Commandes utiles

```bash
ls
pwd
put fichier.txt
get fichier.txt
exit
```

---

# FAIL2BAN

## Installation

```bash
apt install fail2ban -y
```

## Vérifier

```bash
systemctl status fail2ban
```

---

# ALIAS SSH

## Fichier

```bash
nano ~/.ssh/config
```

Exemple :

```bash
Host srv
HostName 192.168.1.10
User melissa
Port 22
```

Connexion :

```bash
ssh srv
```

---

# DÉPANNAGE EXAMEN

```bash
systemctl status ssh
systemctl restart ssh

ss -tulpn | grep ssh

cat /etc/ssh/sshd_config

journalctl -xe
journalctl -u ssh

ping IP_SERVEUR
```

---

# À CONNAÎTRE PAR CŒUR

```bash
apt install openssh-server -y

ssh user@IP

ssh-keygen
ssh-copy-id user@IP

scp fichier user@IP:~

sftp user@IP

nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config

systemctl restart ssh
systemctl status ssh
```

## Ports

```text
SSH  = TCP 22
SFTP = TCP 22
SCP  = TCP 22
```
